---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

// Sections with LaTeX use set:html so Astro doesn't try to parse {} as expressions.
const protocolHtml = String.raw`
    <h2>The Protocol</h2>
    <p>
      The Sudoku ZKP works very similarly to the graph coloring proof. Because every valid
      Sudoku solution remains valid under any relabeling of the digits 1–9, Peggy can hide her
      solution simply by applying a random <strong>digit permutation</strong>
      $\sigma : \{1,\ldots,9\} \to \{1,\ldots,9\}$ before committing.
    </p>

    <h3>Step 1 — Commit</h3>
    <p>
      Peggy permutes her solution with a freshly chosen $\sigma$ and then commits to every
      cell using a cryptographic hash with a random nonce:
    </p>
    $$\text{commit}_{i} = \text{SHA-256}\!\left(\,\sigma(d_i) \;\|\; r_i\,\right)$$
    <p>
      where $d_i$ is the original digit at cell $i$ and $r_i$ is a large random string
      chosen fresh every round. She sends all 81 commitments to Victor. Victor sees 81
      sealed envelopes — he cannot open any of them.
    </p>

    <h3>Step 2 — Challenge</h3>
    <p>
      Victor randomly picks one of <strong>27 challenge groups</strong>: any of the 9 rows,
      9 columns, or 9 subsquares. He may also ask Peggy to reveal all <em>preset</em> cells
      to verify permutation consistency. Each group must contain digits 1–9 exactly once in
      any valid solution.
    </p>

    <h3>Step 3 — Reveal &amp; Verify</h3>
    <p>
      Peggy opens the 9 commitments for the challenged group, disclosing the permuted
      digit and nonce for each. Victor verifies three things:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Every hash matches: $\text{SHA-256}(\sigma(d_i) \| r_i) = \text{commit}_i$</li>
      <li>The 9 revealed digits are all distinct (1–9, each exactly once)</li>
      <li>For preset cells: the permutation $\sigma$ is consistent across the board</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      If Peggy is cheating, at least one row, column, or subsquare contains a duplicate.
      The probability of Victor missing it in a single round is at most $\tfrac{26}{27}$.
      After $k$ independent rounds:
    </p>
    $$P(\text{not caught after } k \text{ rounds}) \;\leq\; \left(\frac{26}{27}\right)^{\!k}$$

    <div class="callout note">
      <div class="callout-label">Why This Is Zero-Knowledge</div>
      Every round uses a fresh random permutation. The 9 digits Victor sees are just some
      arrangement of 1–9 — information he already knew any valid group must contain.
      He learns nothing about the actual digit assignment. A simulator could produce
      identically distributed transcripts without ever seeing the real solution.
    </div>
`;

const postDemoHtml = String.raw`
    <!-- ── 4. How Many Rounds? ── -->
    <h2>How Many Rounds?</h2>
    <p>
      With 27 possible challenge groups, the soundness error per round is $\frac{26}{27} \approx 96.3\%$.
      This decreases exponentially with each round:
    </p>
    <table class="math-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Rounds ($k$)</th>
          <th>Soundness error $\left(\tfrac{26}{27}\right)^k$</th>
          <th>Verifier confidence</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>1</td>  <td>96.3%</td><td>3.7%</td></tr>
        <tr><td>10</td> <td>69.0%</td><td>31.0%</td></tr>
        <tr><td>50</td> <td>15.3%</td><td>84.7%</td></tr>
        <tr><td>100</td><td>2.3%</td> <td>97.7%</td></tr>
        <tr><td>200</td><td>0.06%</td><td>99.94%</td></tr>
        <tr><td>500</td><td>$\approx 10^{-8}$</td><td>$\approx 100\%$</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>
      Compare with graph coloring, which had $\frac{m-1}{m}$ soundness error per round where
      $m$ is the number of edges. For the classic 6-edge example that was $\frac{5}{6} \approx 83.3\%$
      per round — much better per-round guarantees. Sudoku's 27 groups give weaker per-round reduction
      but the protocol applies to a richer, more structured problem.
    </p>

    <div class="page-nav">
      <a href="/chapters/graph-coloring">← Graph Coloring</a>
    </div>
`;
---

<style is:global>
  /* ── Sudoku grid ── */
  .sudoku-wrap { overflow-x: auto; line-height: 0; }

  .sudoku-grid {
    border-collapse: collapse;
    border: 2px solid var(--muted);
  }

  .sudoku-cell {
    width: 38px; height: 38px;
    text-align: center; vertical-align: middle;
    font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 500;
    border: 1px solid #252530;
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--heading);
    transition: background 0.18s, color 0.18s;
    user-select: none;
  }

  .sudoku-cell.box-right  { border-right:  2px solid var(--muted); }
  .sudoku-cell.box-bottom { border-bottom: 2px solid var(--muted); }

  .sudoku-cell.is-preset  { color: var(--accent); font-weight: 700; }
  .sudoku-cell.is-locked  { color: #383850; font-size: 0.75rem; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.012); }

  .sudoku-cell.hl-orange  { background: rgba(196,100,60,0.18); }
  .sudoku-cell.hl-green   { background: rgba(70,160,100,0.16); }
  .sudoku-cell.hl-reveal  { background: rgba(129,140,248,0.15); color: var(--heading); font-weight: 600; }
  .sudoku-cell.hl-green.hl-reveal { background: rgba(70,160,100,0.18); color: var(--heading); font-weight: 600; }

  /* ── Phase progress bar ── */
  .phase-bar { display: flex; gap: 3px; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .phase-step { flex: 1; height: 2px; border-radius: 1px; background: var(--border); transition: background 0.3s; }
  .phase-step.done    { background: var(--muted); }
  .phase-step.current { background: var(--accent); }

  /* ── Demo layout ── */
  .sudoku-demo-body { display: flex; flex-direction: row; gap: 2rem; align-items: flex-start; margin-top: 0.5rem; }
  .sudoku-left  { flex: 0 0 auto; }
  .sudoku-right { flex: 1; min-width: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.8rem; }

  /* ── Info panels ── */
  .info-panel { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.022); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 4px; padding: 0.8rem 1rem; }
  .info-panel-label { font-size: 0.58rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.13em; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 0.55rem; }

  /* ── Permutation mapping chips ── */
  .perm-map { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.35rem; }
  .perm-chip { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.25rem; font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.8rem; padding: 0.18rem 0.55rem; background: var(--bg-code); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 3px; color: var(--text); }
  .perm-chip .arr { color: var(--muted); }

  /* ── Commitment hash mini-grid ── */
  .commit-mini-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(9, 1fr); gap: 2px; }
  .commit-cell { aspect-ratio: 1; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.38rem; background: var(--bg-code); border-radius: 2px; color: #383854; cursor: default; overflow: hidden; transition: background 0.15s; }
  .commit-cell.filled     { color: #5858a0; }
  .commit-cell.highlighted { background: rgba(129,140,248,0.15); color: var(--accent); }

  /* ── Challenge selector ── */
  .challenge-type-row { display: flex; gap: 0.35rem; margin-bottom: 0.55rem; }
  .ctype-btn { flex: 1; padding: 0.28rem 0; font-family: var(--font); font-size: 0.72rem; font-weight: 500; background: transparent; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 3px; color: var(--muted); cursor: pointer; transition: color 0.14s, border-color 0.14s, background 0.14s; }
  .ctype-btn:hover { color: var(--text); border-color: var(--muted); }
  .ctype-btn.sel { color: var(--accent); border-color: var(--accent); background: rgba(129,140,248,0.07); }
  .index-row { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.3rem; margin-bottom: 0.45rem; }
  .idx-btn { width: 26px; height: 26px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.78rem; background: transparent; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 3px; color: var(--muted); cursor: pointer; transition: color 0.14s, border-color 0.14s, background 0.14s; }
  .idx-btn:hover { color: var(--text); border-color: var(--muted); }
  .idx-btn.sel { color: var(--accent); border-color: var(--accent); background: rgba(129,140,248,0.07); }
  .challenge-hint { font-size: 0.76rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.5; }

  /* ── Revealed table ── */
  .reveal-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.74rem; }
  .reveal-table th { font-size: 0.58rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--muted); padding: 0 0.4rem 0.35rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .reveal-table td { padding: 0.18rem 0.4rem; font-family: var(--mono); vertical-align: middle; }
  .reveal-table td:first-child { color: var(--muted); }
  .reveal-table td:nth-child(2) { color: var(--heading); font-weight: 600; font-family: var(--font); }
  .reveal-table td:nth-child(3), .reveal-table td:nth-child(4) { color: #585878; font-size: 0.68rem; }
  .reveal-row-orange { background: rgba(196,100,60,0.08); }
  .reveal-row-green  { background: rgba(70,160,100,0.08); }

  /* ── Verify result ── */
  .verify-check { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.83rem; padding: 0.22rem 0; }
  .check-icon { font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .check-ok   { color: #4fa870; }
  .check-fail { color: #c44444; }

  /* ── Confidence bar ── */
  .conf-bar-wrap { height: 3px; background: var(--border); border-radius: 2px; margin: 0.6rem 0 0.25rem; overflow: hidden; }
  .conf-bar { height: 100%; background: var(--accent); border-radius: 2px; transition: width 0.5s ease; width: 0%; }

  /* ── Mobile ── */
  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .sudoku-demo-body { flex-direction: column; }
    .sudoku-left { width: 100%; display: flex; justify-content: center; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 520px) {
    .sudoku-cell { width: 30px; height: 30px; font-size: 0.85rem; }
    .challenge-type-row { flex-wrap: wrap; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 380px) {
    .sudoku-cell { width: 26px; height: 26px; font-size: 0.78rem; }
  }
</style>

<BaseLayout
  title="Sudoku ZKP — ZK Proofs"
  crumb="Interactive · Sudoku ZKP"
  useKatex
  extraScript="/js/sudoku-demo.js"
>
  <div class="content">

    <div class="page-meta">Interactive · Demos</div>
    <h1>Sudoku Zero-Knowledge Proof</h1>

    <p>
      Sudoku solutions can be proven via zero-knowledge proof. If Peggy has a solution to
      Victor's puzzle, she can convince him her solution is valid without ever revealing
      the solution — or any information about it beyond its existence.
    </p>

    <!-- ── 1. The Setup ── -->
    <h2>The Setup</h2>
    <p>Two parties:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Peggy (Prover)</strong> — has a valid solution to a Sudoku puzzle.</li>
      <li><strong>Victor (Verifier)</strong> — has the puzzle and wants proof the solution exists,
          but Peggy won't reveal it without payment.</li>
    </ul>

    <!-- ── 2. The Protocol (LaTeX) ── -->
    <Fragment set:html={protocolHtml} />

    <!-- ── 3. Interactive Demo ── -->
    <h2>Try It Yourself</h2>
    <p>
      The demo below runs a real instance of the protocol. You act as both Peggy and Victor.
      Hashes are genuine SHA-256 digests computed in your browser via the Web Crypto API.
    </p>

    <figure>
    <section class="demo-section" id="sudokuDemo" aria-label="Interactive Sudoku ZKP demo">
      <div class="demo-inner">

        <div style="display:flex; align-items:flex-start; justify-content:space-between; gap:1rem; flex-wrap:wrap; margin-bottom:1rem;">
          <div>
            <span class="demo-eyebrow">Interactive Demo</span>
            <div class="demo-title">Sudoku ZKP Protocol</div>
            <p class="demo-desc" id="demoMsg">Click <strong>Begin Protocol</strong> to start a round.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="demo-stats" style="margin:0; border:none; padding:0; gap:1.5rem; flex-shrink:0;">
            <div class="demo-stat">
              <div class="demo-stat-value" id="statRounds">0</div>
              <div class="demo-stat-label">Rounds</div>
            </div>
            <div class="demo-stat">
              <div class="demo-stat-value" id="statConf">—</div>
              <div class="demo-stat-label">Confidence</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="phase-bar">
          <div class="phase-step current" id="ps0"></div>
          <div class="phase-step" id="ps1"></div>
          <div class="phase-step" id="ps2"></div>
          <div class="phase-step" id="ps3"></div>
          <div class="phase-step" id="ps4"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="sudoku-demo-body">
          <div class="sudoku-left">
            <div class="sudoku-wrap">
              <div id="sudokuGridWrap"></div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="sudoku-right">

            <div id="panelSetup">
              <div class="info-panel">
                <div class="info-panel-label">The Problem</div>
                <p style="font-size:0.83rem; color:var(--text); line-height:1.7; margin:0;">
                  Victor has this Sudoku puzzle (highlighted cells in
                  <span style="color:var(--accent); font-weight:600;">indigo</span> are the presets).
                  Peggy claims to have a valid solution and will prove it
                  without showing a single digit of her answer.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div id="panelCommitted" style="display:none;">
              <div class="info-panel" style="margin-bottom:0.7rem;">
                <div class="info-panel-label">Peggy's Digit Permutation (secret)</div>
                <div class="perm-map" id="permMap"></div>
              </div>
              <div class="info-panel">
                <div class="info-panel-label">81 SHA-256 Commitments sent to Victor</div>
                <div class="commit-mini-grid" id="commitMiniGrid"></div>
                <p style="font-size:0.68rem; color:var(--muted); margin-top:0.45rem; line-height:1.5;">
                  Each cell is a SHA-256 hash of <code>permuted_digit‑nonce</code>.
                  Hover to see the full hash.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div id="panelChallenge" style="display:none;">
              <div class="info-panel">
                <div class="info-panel-label">Victor's Challenge</div>
                <div class="challenge-type-row" id="ctypeRow">
                  <button class="ctype-btn sel" data-t="row">Row</button>
                  <button class="ctype-btn" data-t="column">Column</button>
                  <button class="ctype-btn" data-t="square">Box</button>
                  <button class="ctype-btn" data-t="preset">Presets</button>
                </div>
                <div class="index-row" id="idxRow"></div>
                <p class="challenge-hint" id="challengeHint">Pick a row for Peggy to open.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="info-panel">
                <div class="info-panel-label">Commitments (highlighted = will be opened)</div>
                <div class="commit-mini-grid" id="commitMiniGrid2"></div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div id="panelRevealed" style="display:none;">
              <div class="info-panel">
                <div class="info-panel-label">Revealed Values &amp; Nonces</div>
                <div id="revealedTableWrap" style="overflow-y:auto; max-height:220px;">
                  <table class="reveal-table" id="revealedTable">
                    <thead>
                      <tr>
                        <th>Cell</th>
                        <th>Value</th>
                        <th>Nonce (prefix)</th>
                        <th>Commit (prefix)</th>
                      </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody id="revealedBody"></tbody>
                  </table>
                </div>
                <p style="font-size:0.68rem; color:var(--muted); margin-top:0.45rem;">
                  <span style="display:inline-block; width:8px; height:8px; background:rgba(196,100,60,0.3); border-radius:1px; margin-right:4px;"></span>orange = challenged group &nbsp;
                  <span style="display:inline-block; width:8px; height:8px; background:rgba(70,160,100,0.3); border-radius:1px; margin-right:4px;"></span>green = consistency check
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div id="panelVerified" style="display:none;">
              <div class="info-panel">
                <div class="info-panel-label">Verification Result</div>
                <div id="verifyChecks"></div>
                <div class="conf-bar-wrap">
                  <div class="conf-bar" id="confBar"></div>
                </div>
                <p style="font-size:0.7rem; color:var(--muted); margin:0; line-height:1.5;">
                  Verifier confidence that Peggy has a valid solution (assuming she could be cheating).
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="demo-actions" style="margin-top:1.2rem;">
          <button class="demo-action-btn" id="actionBtn" onclick="handleAction()">Begin Protocol</button>
          <button class="demo-again-btn" id="resetBtn" onclick="resetDemo()" style="display:none;">Reset</button>
        </div>

      </div>

      <p class="demo-caption">
        <strong>Figure 2.</strong> &ensp;Interactive simulation of the Sudoku ZKP protocol.
        SHA-256 hashes are computed via the Web Crypto API in your browser.
        Protocol design based on
        <a href="https://manishearth.github.io/blog/2016/08/10/interactive-sudoku-zero-knowledge-proof/">
          Manish Goregaokar's Sudoku ZKP</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
    </figure>

    <!-- Section 4 + page nav contain LaTeX — rendered via set:html -->
    <Fragment set:html={postDemoHtml} />

  </div>
</BaseLayout>
